The paper introduces a new model for massively parallel computation that involves distributed data storage and random read access. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Parallel and Distributed Computing (cs.PD) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper presents new graph algorithms with improved round complexities, which suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
